Download Manager README
-----------------------------------------------------

To run this script:

python3 kodex.py --arg1 --arg2

Use --help to see all available arguments

i.e. py3 dm.py --help

-----------------------------------------------------

This package requires:
* Python 3.4+
* Python Requests package
* Python jsonrpcclient package
* Python Django package
* Python dj_static package

-----------------------------------------------------

Use pip to install Python third-party package:

* python3 -m pip install jsonrpcclient

To install this on Synology NAS the pip package must be installed first:

* Download get-pip.py to NAS downloads folder (google python pip for more info)
* SSH into DiskStation as root user: ssh root@$DISKSTATION
* Change directory to get-pip.py directory (e.g. cd /volume1/downloads/)
* Execute get-pip script: python3 get-pip.py
* Proceed with package install as before (e.g. python3 -m pip install jsonrpcclient)

-----------------------------------------------------

Further Synology Diskstation set-up:

This needs a django supporting web server.
* Python Gunicorn package (Suggested)

Add start-on-boot script:
* Copy kodex.sh to /usr/local/etc/rc.d

-----------------------------------------------------

After fresh install the django database must be setup using:

python3 manage.py migrate

To access admin page navigate to <IP>/admin. Login details will need to be created:

python3 manage.py createsuperuser ("admin"/"super" - blank - "password")


